Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a generous pinch of @salt{} on to boil for the pasta. Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1/2}(peeled and chopped roughly into ½cm cubes). Peel and finely grate the @garlic clove{1}(finely grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, then remove the core from the @yellow pepper{1/2}(halved and core removed), and cut into ½cm slices. Pick the @basil{} leaves from their stalks and set aside. Finely chop the stalks. Pop your #kettle{} on to boil.

Put a splash of @olive oil{} in another large saucepan on high heat. When the oil is hot, add the @British beef mince{250%g} and use a #wooden spoon{} to break it up. Cook until nicely browned, ~{5%minutes}. Season with a pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{}. Add the onion and pepper. Cook until soft, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, @dried thyme{} and @tomato puree{}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @tomato passata{}, stir and reduce the heat to low.

Dissolve the @beef stock pot{} in boiling @water{300%ml} and add this to the pan. Bring the ragu to the boil, then lower the heat and add the chopped basil stalks. Leave to simmer for ~{20%minutes}. The ragu will reduce and thicken in this time.

Add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} to your pan of boiling water. Cook for ~{11%minutes} or until al dente.

> Al dente simply means the pasta is cooked through but has a tiny bit of firmness left in the middle.

While the pasta is cooking, prepare the salsa. Finely chop the @pitted black olives{50%g}(finely chopped) and chop the @vine tomatoes{1}(chopped into ½cm cubes). Pop them in a #mixing bowl{} with the @olive oil{}\(for salsa) (about 1 tbsp). Tear over half the @basil leaves{} and mix in.

When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} (reserve a splash of the cooking water). Taste the ragu and season with more @salt{} and @black pepper{} if necessary. Tear in the remaining basil leaves. Combine with the cooked pasta and mix well (add a little of the cooking water if you think it looks too dry). Serve in deep #bowls{}, topped with the salsa and sprinkled with @grated hard Italian style cheese{}. Enjoy!